{[#]White to move and draw} 46. Bf3 $2 {White has to exchange the roles of his
defending pieces, i.e. the king should take care of the wrong rook's pawn and
the bishop should stop the c-pawn.} ({So the monarch has to get on its way at
once:} 46. Kd3 Kf4 (46... h5 47. Ke2 Bd4 48. Kf3 $11) 47. Ke2 Bd4 (47... Kg3
48. Bf3 c4 49. Bh5 Bd4 50. Bf7 c3 51. Kd3 Bf6 52. Bh5 Kh4 53. Bd1 h5 54. Ke3
$11) 48. Bf3 (48. Kf1 $2 Kg3 $19) 48... c4 49. Bh5 Kg5 50. Bf7 c3 51. Bb3 Kf4 (
51... h5 52. Kf3 $11) 52. Bf7 Kg4 53. Be6+ Kg3 54. Bf7 Bb6 55. Bh5 Ba5 56. Kd3
Kh4 57. Bf3 h5 58. Bd1 Kg5 59. Ke2 $11) 46... h5 47. Kd3 h4 48. Ke2 Bd4 $1 {
It is very important that White should not be allowed a changing of the guard.
For that reason} (48... Bg3 $2 {would be a decisive mistake:} 49. Bd5 h3 50.
Kf1 h2 51. Kg2 $11 {and the white king has the h-pawn under control, so that
the bishop can be sacrificed for the c-pawn. Because the wrong rook's pawn
cannot get though, e.g.} Kf4 52. Kh1 Ke3 53. Be6 Kd4 54. Bf7 c4 55. Bxc4 Kxc4
56. Kg2 Kd3 57. Kh1 Ke2 58. Kg2 Ke3 59. Kh1 $11) 49. Bd5 (49. Kf1 h3 $19) 49...
Kf4 50. Kf1 Kg3 51. Be6 h3 52. Bd5 h2 53. Ke2 c4 54. Bh1 c3 55. Bc6 Bb6 56. Bh1
Ba5 {and Lilit Galojan resigned, because after} 57. Be4 (57. Kd3 Kf2 $19) 57...
c2 $19 {her bishop is overloaded.} 0-1

